 <H1>Principle: Be Careful</H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Identify (& Justify) every trust decision
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Can be buried in operational logic
</UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Example: Is Scooter a Member?
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>W3C has Public, Member, and Team web access
<LI>Originally, Member IP address masks were used
<LI>Verbal contracts trusted employees to protect info
<LI>AltaVistaï¿½s web crawler was seen as a Member
<UL></P>

<P><LI>... And information leaked out to the index!
</UL><LI>Required coordination of password database, filesystem permissions, and Robot Exclusion file</UL></UL></P>

